Analyze Your Data

Drill Down into Your Reports to Learn Even More

Drill-down helps you take a closer look at records in a report. For example, as a sales manager, drill-down can help you track the progress of just a few of your reps or review the breakdown of current opportunities based on type.

To drill down into a report:

Run a report that includes at least one-row grouping.
Select checkboxes for the particular values that you want to drill in to.
Click Drill Down.
The primary row group for your report is preselected in the Group by field. To change the grouping, click X and select a different field.
Click Apply.

If you edit the report and open the Filters tab, you can see that a filter was added for the values you selected.
title: Drill Down in Salesforce Reports
